  "response": "To score well in physics for AIPMT (now NEET), follow these strategies:\n\n1. Study Plan\n- Cover entire NCERT textbook thoroughly\n- Use reference books like HC Verma or DC Pandey\n- Make a structured study schedule\n\n2. Key Topics to Focus\n- Mechanics\n- Electromagnetism\n- Modern Physics\n- Optics\n- Thermodynamics\n\n3. Preparation Techniques\n- Understand concepts, not just memorize\n- Practice numerical problems\n- Solve previous years' question papers\n- Take mock tests regularly\n\n4. Important Tips\n- Develop strong mathematical skills\n- Practice time management\n- Focus on problem-solving techniques\n- Learn formula derivations\n- Solve numerical problems systematically\n\n5. Recommended Books\n- NCERT Physics textbook\n- HC Verma\n- Concepts of Physics by DC Pandey\n- Physics guide by Cengage\n- Objective Physics by DC Pandey\n\n6. Additional Strategies\n- Make short notes\n- Revise regularly\n- Analyze your weak areas\n- Join online/offline test series\n- Stay consistent and motivated\n\nRemember, consistent practice and conceptual clarity are key to scoring well in physics.",
